<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--EGermany-NATO,0181</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>East German Truck Delivers NATO Building Supplies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COPENHAGEN, Denmark (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A trucking company from East Germany,
a Soviet bloc country, delivered building material for bombproof
aircraft hangars to a NATO military installation in Denmark, a
newspaper reported.
   An East German truck driven by two East Germans pulled up to the
guardhouse of Tirstrup airbase in west Denmark Nov. 3 with documents
showing that the supplies came from neutral Austria, the
Jyllands-Posten daily said Wednesday.
   The materials were for hangers meant to protect NATO warplanes
from bombers of the Soviet-bloc alliance, the Warsaw Pact.
   ``We thought it was an Austrian company that would deliver the
materials. So we were much taken aback when we learned that the
order had gone to an East German firm,'' the paper quoted base
commander Lt. Col. Egon Baek as saying.
   The truck was unloaded outside the base, the report said.
   A spokesman for the entrepreneur firm WTK, one of the contracters
building the 71 reinforced hangars, said the Austrian supplier had
hired the East German transport company.
</TEXT>
