<FILEID>AP-NR-11-24-88 0718EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     11-24 0376</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0387</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Snow Advisories Issued For Several Western, Midwestern States</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Snow advisories were posted this morning for the mountains of
eastern Oregon and California, and parts of Idaho, Utah, Montana,
Wyoming and North Dakota.
   For the mountains of Southern California and for northern
Arizona, advisories also were issued for gusty winds.
   Snow extended from south-central Montana across northern and
western Wyoming, eastern Idaho, northern Utah and northern Nevada.
The biggest reported snowfall for the six hours ended 1 a.m. EST was
4 inches at Reno, Nev.
   Rain lingered this morning along the northern and central Pacific
Coast, from eastern Montana into western North Dakota, as well as
eastern Florida, Georgia, and along the central Atlantic Coast.
   Today's weather forecast called for rain along the northern half
of the Pacific Coast and across the central part of the Dakotas;
snow from the western part of the Dakotas across the upper Missouri
Valley and the Rockies.
   Predicted highs: 20s and 30s in New England, northern Minnesota,
North Dakota and the Rockies; 40s and 50s from New York state across
Virginia, the Great Lakes, the Ohio Valley, the upper Mississippi
Valley, South Dakota, Nebraska, and the northern two-thirds of the
Pacific Coast; 80s in southern Florida and southern Texas.
   The rest of the nation should generally be in the 60s and 70s.
   The nation's temperatures at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 15 degrees at
Houlton, Maine, to 75 at Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 45 fair; Boston 30 cloudy; Buffalo 26 partly
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 50 partly cloudy; Cincinnati 29 fair;
Cleveland 27 fair; Detroit 27 foggy; Miami 70 foggy; New York 35
fair; Philadelphia 34 fair; Pittsburgh 27 fair; Portland, Maine 25
fair; Washington 36 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 23 cloudy; Chicago 37 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
45 fair; Denver 58 windy; Des Moines 41 fair; Indianapolis 35 fair;
Kansas City 46 windy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 38 partly cloudy;
Nashville 32 fair; New Orleans 44 foggy; St. Louis 41 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 36 fair; Anchorage 15 cloudy; Las Vegas 55
windy; Los Angeles 53 partly cloudy; Phoenix 55 fair; Salt Lake City
