<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Thailand-Flood     11-24 0134</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Thailand-Flood,0138</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Floods Hit Thailand's Southern Provinces, 22 Die</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four days of storms and monsoon flooding
in southern Thailand have killed 22 people and damaged nearly a
thousand roads, government officials said today.
   Since Saturday the storms also have destroyed 218 bridges and 67
dikes and irrigation works in 11 provinces of the southern
peninsula, according to officials of the Interior Ministry and
Meteorological Bureau.
   More than 120,000 acres of farmland were reported under water.
   A local newspaper quoted Lt. Gen. Kitti Rattanachaya, deputy
commander of the Fourth Army Region, as troops have been dispatched
to evacuate villagers isolated by floods.
   The English-language Nation also reported that the Thai air force
is airlifting supplies to flood-hit areas, and the Local
Administration department has allocated $1.4 million for relief
operations.
</TEXT>
