<HEAD>Hungary Expels Romanian Diplomat</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New thruout to CORRECT that Platona political diplomat. No
pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hungary today expelled a Romanian
diplomat in retaliation for Romania's decision to send a Hungarian
commerical counselor home, the official MTI news agency reported.
   Hungary expelled Romanian political counselor Pavel Platona, MTI
said. On Saturday, Romania ordered Hungarian Commercial Counselor
Karoly Gyorfy to leave. The moves further strained the already tense
relations between the two neighboring Warsaw Pact allies.
   A formal Hungarian protest note over the explusion of Gyorfy was
delivered today to the Romanian Embassy in Budapest.
   According to MTI, the note stated that, ``as a response'' to
Gyorfy's expulsion, Platona was declared persona non grata and given
72 hours to leave.
   Last summer Romania expelled the staff of the Hungarian Consulate
at Cluj-Napoca in Transylvania and declared the operation closed
following a demonstration in Budapest by about 50,000 people
protesting Romanian policies.
   Hungarians have expressed anger and concern for the welfare of
1.7 million ethnic Hungarians living in Romania, alleging the
minority suffers discrimination and other hardships.
