<HEAD>Dutch Navy Rescues Fisherman, 3 Sons</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dutch sailors rescued an Indonesian
fisherman and his three sons who were floating in the Malacca Strait
for about 12 hours, the Netherlands Embassy said Thursday.
   The royal Dutch navy's HMS Witte de With was on its way from
Australia to the Netherlands when it found the four in the sea
Tuesday after their fishing boat sank, the embassy said.
   It said three of the four were in good condition; the fourth was
suffering from exhaustion. It did not specify who was suffering from
exhaustion.
   They were dropped off at Sigli port in north Sumatra on Wednesday.
   Ali Putie, and his sons Ramuli, 22; Murmaban, 19; and Umar, 16,
are believed to have left Belawan port on Sumatra's north coast
Monday with their fishing boat Kasuma Jaya, which capsized that
night.
