<2ND_LINE>AM-Golden Fleece,230</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>For Release at 6:30 p.m. EST - time set by source</NOTE>
<HEAD>Proxmire Award To Follow Retiring Senator To Taypayers Union</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Retiring Sen. William Proxmire, D-Wis., has
been elected to the board of the National Taxpayers Union and will
continue sponsoring his ``Golden Fleece Award'' in the new role, the
group announced Thursday.
   Proxmire did not seek re-election and will become a former
senator when the new Congress is sworn in next month.
   ``We are delighted to welcome Senator Proxmire to the NTU
board,'' said Jim Davidson, chairman of the not-for-profit gadfly
organization. ``His integrity and long-standing dedication to the
rights of taxpayers is well known and we are honored to have him
associated with the work of NTU.''
   Davidson said that starting in January, Proxmire will supervise
his monthly ``Golden Fleece Award'' in cooperation with the
Taxpayers Union.
   ``I am pleased to join the board of NTU, which I regard as the
most effective lobby in Washington working for the benefit of the
general taxpaying public,'' Proxmire said in a statement distributed
by the organization.
   Proxmire, who was in the Senate for 32 years, started giving out
his monthly ``Golden Fleece Award'' in 1975 for what he termed the
``biggest example of ridiculous, ironic, or wasteful spending'' by a
government agency.
   The NTU, which calls itself a ``taxpayer-advocacy organization,''
was founded in 1969 and claims 150,000 members.
</TEXT>
